ent right margin, suggesting line ends are preserved. The letters on the fourth fragment are smaller, and preserve vacat to the left suggesting line beginning. A further line is partially preserved on the fourth fragment.",{"_":35,"ana":36,"ref":37},{"lettering":406,"dimensions":407},"The letters are fairly regularly cut, with almost no serifs/terminations to the strokes, excpt for the slight extension of the apex of alpha and delta. Alpha has broken bar; omicron is slightly ovoid and full size; pi has equal length verticals; epsilon is lunate; phi is rhomboid.",[408,410,414,416],{"type":43,"l":44,"from":45,"to":45,"h":409,"unit":46,"atLeast":409,"atMost":409},"12",{"type":43,"l":411,"from":50,"to":50,"h":412,"unit":46,"atLeast":409,"atMost":413},"Line 2","12-14","14",{"type":48,"l":49,"from":45,"to":50,"h":415,"unit":46,"atLeast":415,"atMost":415},"2",{"type":48,"l":417,"from":50,"to":418,"h":419,"unit":46,"atLeast":420,"atMost":415},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","line3","1-2","1",{"_":422,"notBefore":361,"notAfter":423,"evidence":143},"4th century CE",400,[425,426],{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},{"_":61,"type":62,"ref":63},[428],[66,67],[],{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":72,"mainLang":73,"languages":432},[72],{"n":77,"url":434,"height":79,"width":80,"desc":81,"surfaceType":82},"ISic004390_tiled.tif",[436,438,440,442],{"atLeast":437,"atMost":437},12,{"atLeast":437,"atMost":439},14,{"atLeast":441,"atMost":441},2,{"atLeast":443,"atMost":441},1,[445,446],"Tréziny, 2011, À propos d’une inscription funéraire paléochrétienne de Mégara Hyblaea","Tréziny, 2018, Mégara Hyblaea. 7, La ville classique, hellénistique et romaine",[448,449],"DFXDQ8GT","5UHWUE4K",[451,452,453,120,394,454,108,109,110,111,108,112,113,73],"isic004390","fragmentary early christian funerary inscription",{"_":391},"marble","\u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aa-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>τ]ό παιδὶον \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[ὃς ἀπὲθανε] τῇ πρό \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ε\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[εἰδῶν Σεπτε]μβρὶων \u003Cbr id=\"aa-l4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[ζῆσας ἔτη\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">fragment (physical) b\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"ab-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>φα[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":457,"uri":457,"title":458,"status":459,"editionAuthor":21,"type":460,"objectType":464,"material":468,"condition":131,"layoutDesc":469,"handNote":473,"date":487,"places":491,"geo":494,"provenance":57,"provenanceGeo":496,"country":10,"region":69,"settlement":57,"repository":499,"idno":500,"textLang":503,"tmNumber":131,"facsimile":505,"letterHeights":507,"publications":515,"zotero":516,"keywords":517,"html":521},"ISic004405","Small altar dedicated to Aphrodite",{"_":20},{"_":461,"ana":462,"ref":463},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":465,"ana":466,"ref":467},"altar","#object.altar","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html",{"_":27,"ana":28,"ref":29},{"layout":470},{"p":471,"rs":472,"damage":131},"Three lines of Greek letters are incised into the front face, occupying most of the space between the mouldings, with a more or less consistent left margin and an uneven right margin",{"_":35,"ana":36,"ref":37},{"lettering":474,"dimensions":475},"The letters are somewhat unevenly incised. Horizontals on alpha and eta often slope down to the left; epsilon is lunate; theta is roughly circulate with a detached horizontal bar in the centre; mu is unevenly incised, with a middle stroke which does not descend all the way.",[476,481,484],{"type":43,"l":477,"from":45,"to":418,"h":478,"unit":46,"atLeast":479,"atMost":480},"Line 1-3","3-7","3","7",{"type":48,"l":49,"from":45,"to":50,"h":482,"unit":46,"atLeast":415,"atMost":483},"2-4","4",{"type":48,"l":417,"from":50,"to":418,"h":485,"unit":46,"atLeast":486,"atMost":415},"0-2","0",{"_":488,"notBefore":489,"notAfter":490,"evidence":143},"2nd — 1st century BCE",-200,-1,[492,493],{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},{"_":61,"type":62,"ref":63},[495],[66,67],[497,498],37.204466,15.181895,{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":501,"type":502},"MH C22","inventory",{"_":72,"mainLang":73,"languages":504},[72],{"n":77,"url":506,"height":79,"width":80,"desc":81,"surfaceType":82},"ISic004405_tiled.tif",[508,511,513],{"atLeast":509,"atMost":510},3,7,{"atLeast":441,"atMost":512},4,{"atLeast":514,"atMost":441},0,[446],[449],[518,519,520,461,465,27,108,109,110,111,108,112,113,73],"isic004405","small altar dedicated to aphrodite",{"_":20},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Μη\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>τριου \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ἀνάθεμα \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Ἀφροδίτη \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":523,"uri":523,"title":524,"status":525,"editionAuthor":21,"type":526,"objectType":527,"material":528,"condition":131,"layoutDesc":529,"handNote":533,"date":538,"places":542,"geo":545,"provenance":57,"provenanceGeo":547,"country":10,"region":69,"settlement":57,"reposito